 The incident happened on Wednesday afternoon. On the video three men can be seen entering Uncle George Take Aways in Cowen Ntuli Street. They pose as customers and buy cigarettes. A screenshot of the video footage showing one of the suspects behind the petrol attendants. The robbers pointed firearms at the cashier as well as his shop assistants. They stole money from the till as well as two cellphones. Two residents, who followed the robbers and managed to catch one, were injured when the captured robber’s friend turned around to save him and opened fire on them.
Both were rushed to hospital and have since been discharged. A closer view of one of the suspects. The gang of robbers seen on the video, also reportedly tried to hijack a car after they shot the two people and fled down Cowen Ntuli Street. They are also suspected of being involved in other robberies in neighbouring towns. If you have any information that can assist the police in tracing the robbers, contact const. Mtsweni on 072 947 3661.   R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za